    , parseVttTime
    , parseSpriteVtt
    )


{-| Production-ready video player for Canopy.

Orchestrates HLS/DASH adaptive streaming, accessible keyboard-navigable
controls, captions with full VTT positioning and inline markup, seek
thumbnail preview via frame capture or sprite sheets, auto-hiding controls,
responsive compact mode, auto-pause on scroll, live stream detection,
chapter markers, touch gesture controls, drag-to-scrub, mobile double-tap
seeking, autoplay failure handling, exponential retry backoff, ARIA
accessibility announcements, and analytics OutMsg hooks.

Follows The Elm Architecture: `init` creates the initial state,
`update` handles messages, `subscriptions` wires browser observers,
and `view` renders the HTML.

# State
@docs State, Msg, OutMsg, ActiveMenu, QualityLevel
@docs ChapterCue, ThumbnailSprite
@docs HlsInternalMsg, DashInternalMsg, ThumbnailInternalMsg

# TEA
@docs init, update, subscriptions, view

# Accessors
@docs currentTime, duration, paused, buffered, bufferAhead, totalBuffered
@docs currentQuality, availableQualities, captionTracks
@docs controlsVisible, lastError, remoteAvailable, hasError
@docs isLive, isFullscreen, isPip, isCompact, fullscreenUnavailable, activeMenu
@docs thumbnailDataUrl, thumbnailCapturing
@docs playbackRate, volume, muted, activeCaptionTrack, chapters, thumbnailSprites
@docs keyboardHelpVisible, parseVttTime, parseSpriteVtt

-}


